    "what_description": "Cinchona pubescens is a tropical tree species in the family Rubiaceae, native to the Andean regions of South America. It grows up to 10 meters tall, with a straight stem and a rounded crown, and has pubescent young branches and leaves. The leaves are opposite, elliptical to lanceolate, 10-30 cm long, and 3-8 cm wide, with a pointed apex and an entire margin. The inflorescence is a terminal, cylindrical spike, 5-10 cm long, bearing small, greenish-white flowers. The tree is cultivated for its bark, which contains the alkaloids quinine and quinidine.",
