    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Cinchona pubescens are antimalarial, with the plant containing quinine as a major bioactive compound responsible for its efficacy against Plasmodium falciparum. The plant's anti-inflammatory properties are attributed to the presence of flavonoids, which have been shown to exhibit significant inhibition of pro-inflammatory enzymes. Additionally, the antioxidant properties of Cinchona pubescens are a result of its content of phenolic compounds, such as caffeic acid and ferulic acid, which are known to neutralize free radicals. The antipyretic properties of the plant are due to its ability to lower body temperature by inhibiting the release of pyrogenic substances, a function that is also attributed to its bioactive compounds. The analgesic properties of Cinchona pubescens are associated with its content of saponins, which have been found to exhibit significant pain-relieving activity.",
