    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Cinchona pubescens are quinine, quinidine, quinic acid, quinovic acid, and cinchonine, which are responsible for its medicinal properties due to their ability to act on the human body in various ways. Quinine is a well-known antimalarial agent that works by interfering with the parasite's ability to digest hemoglobin, while quinidine is a cardiac anti-arrhythmic agent that stabilizes heart rhythms and prevents irregular heartbeats. Quinic acid is a potent antioxidant that helps protect the body from oxidative stress and inflammation, and quinovic acid is a known inhibitor of the enzyme alpha-glucosidase, which helps regulate blood sugar levels. Cinchonine, on the other hand, is a vasodilator that helps relax blood vessels and improve blood flow, which can help lower blood pressure and alleviate symptoms of conditions such as angina. These constituents work together to provide Cinchona pubescens with its anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and cardiovascular protective effects.",
